    "# Peak Coverage\n",
    "\n",
    "Draw peak on Hi-C contact matrix."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import coolbox\n",
    "from coolbox.api import *"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [

      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "coolbox.__version__"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "HiCPeaks Coverage accept bedpe format:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "test_cool = \"../../../tests/test_data/cool_chr9_4000000_6000000.mcool\"\n",
    "test_peak = \"../../../tests/test_data/peak_chr9_4000000_6000000.bedpe\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "frame = XAxis() + \\\n",
    "    Cool(test_cool) + \\\n",
    "    HiCPeaks(test_peak, color=\"#2255ff\", line_width=5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "frame.plot(\"chr9:4000000-6000000\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Parameters:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "    Hi-C Peaks(Loops) Coverge is a special kind of Coverage.\n",
      "    Used to show the peaks on the Hi-C interaction map.\n",
      "\n",
      "    Parameters\n",
      "    ----------\n",
      "    file_ : str\n",
      "        Path to the loop file, loop file is a tab splited text file, fields:\n",
      "        chr1, x1, x2, chr2, y1, y2, [color], ... (other optional fields)\n",
      "\n",
      "    color : str, optional\n",
      "        Peak color, use 'bed_rgb' for specify color in file,\n",
      "        default 'bed_rgb'.\n",
      "\n",
      "    alpha : float, optional\n",
      "        Peak alpha value, default 0.6.\n",
      "\n",
      "    line_width : float, optional\n",
      "        Peak border line width, default 1.0\n",
      "\n",
      "    line_style : str, optional\n",
      "        Border line style, default 'solid'\n",
      "\n",
      "    fill : bool, optional\n",
      "        Fill center or not, default False.\n",
      "\n",
      "    fill_color : str, optional\n",
      "        Fill color, use 'bed_rgb' for specify color in file,\n",
      "        default 'bed_rgb'.\n",
      "\n",
      "    side : {'upper', 'lower', 'both'}\n",
      "        Plot peak in which side of the matrix.\n",
      "        NOTE: This parameters is useful only if the Cool track in matrix format.\n",
      "    \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(HiCPeaks.__doc__)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### CLI code"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%bash\n",
    "\n",
    "coolbox add XAxis - \\\n",
    "add Cool ../../../tests/test_data/cool_chr9_4000000_6000000.mcool - \\\n",
    "add HiCPeaks ../../../tests/test_data/peak_chr9_4000000_6000000.bedpe - \\\n",
    "goto \"chr9:4700000-5600000\" - \\\n",
    "plot /tmp/test_coolbox_hicpeak.png"
   ]
  }
